cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on learning deep representations of medical images using a Siamese CNN architecture for content-based image retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks and requires less supervision for training, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the learned image representations on a task of content-based medical image retrieval, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of deep neural networks for learning image representations also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
